    Given a string "text", return its md5 hash equiv a lent string with length be ing 32 .
    If "text" is an empty st ring, return  Optio nal.empty().

    >>> stringToMd5("Hello world") == "3e25960a79dbc69b674cd4ec67a72c62"
     */
    public Optional<String> stringToMd5(String text) throws NoSuchAlgorithmException {

canonical_solution:
        if (text.isEmpty()) {
            return Optional.empty();
